Preparing your files for tagging

Before we start

The goal of this tutorial is to teach you how to prepare your files for tagging using either the CROW tool or the AntLab tools. You will need to download:

     1. Corpus Text Processor from CROW

  • In order to run the tagger, you will need to convert and standardize your text. For this, we will use the Corpus Text Processor. You can read more about it here

     2. AntLab Tools

  • If you need to convert files from Word or PDF to .txt, download the AntConverter
  • To make sure your files are in the correct encoding, download EncodeAnt

For both programs, remember to download the correct tool for your computer’s operational system.

Overview

In this tutorial, I will explain how to use both the Corpus Text Processor from CROW and the AntLab Tools, but you should choose only one.

      1.Corpus Text Processor from CROW
      2.AntLab Tools

1. Corpus Text Processor

We will use CROW’s Corpus Text Processor to prepare the files. I recommend that you create three folders in your computer that mirror the menus in the Corpus Text Processor: 01_converted, 02_encoded, and 03_standardized before running the tool. It should look like this.

And this is what you will see when you open the Corpus Text Processor

To convert the files, we should follow the order of the menus in the Corpus Text Processor. You can also watch the video demonstration on how to run it.

2. AntLab Tools

2.1. Converting
  • Open AntFileConverter
  • Select the directory where your files are.

File> Open Dir..

  • Press Start

2.2. Encoding

  • Open EncodeAnt

  • Select the directory where your files are.

File> Open File(s)/Open Dir..

  • Click on Convert to UTF-8

  • Press Start
Send us the converted and encoded files for tagging
